 274:../Drivers/cmw_camera/sensors/cmw_imx335.c ****   /* Note: According to the IMX335 datasheet (E18112A84), the power-on sequence
 275:../Drivers/cmw_camera/sensors/cmw_imx335.c ****    * should be as followed:
 276:../Drivers/cmw_camera/sensors/cmw_imx335.c ****    * 1. Turn On the power supplies so that the power supplies rise in order of
 277:../Drivers/cmw_camera/sensors/cmw_imx335.c ****    *    1.2V power supply (DVDD),
 278:../Drivers/cmw_camera/sensors/cmw_imx335.c ****    *    1.8V power supply (OVDD),
 279:../Drivers/cmw_camera/sensors/cmw_imx335.c ****    *    2.9V power supply (AVDD)
 280:../Drivers/cmw_camera/sensors/cmw_imx335.c ****    *   with a rise time of 0 to 200ms.
 281:../Drivers/cmw_camera/sensors/cmw_imx335.c ****    *   In addition, all power supplies should finish rising within 200ms.
 282:../Drivers/cmw_camera/sensors/cmw_imx335.c ****    * 2. The register values are undefined immediately after power-on, so the
 283:../Drivers/cmw_camera/sensors/cmw_imx335.c ****    *    system must be cleared. Hold XCLR at Low level for 500 ns or more after
 284:../Drivers/cmw_camera/sensors/cmw_imx335.c ****    *    all the power supplies have finished rising. (The register values after
 285:../Drivers/cmw_camera/sensors/cmw_imx335.c ****    *    a system clear are the default values.)
 286:../Drivers/cmw_camera/sensors/cmw_imx335.c ****    * 3. The system clear is applied by setting XCLR to High level. The master
 287:../Drivers/cmw_camera/sensors/cmw_imx335.c ****    *    clock input after setting the XCLR pin to High level.
 288:../Drivers/cmw_camera/sensors/cmw_imx335.c ****    * 4. Make the sensor setting by register communication after the system
 289:../Drivers/cmw_camera/sensors/cmw_imx335.c ****    *    clear.
 290:../Drivers/cmw_camera/sensors/cmw_imx335.c ****    *
 291:../Drivers/cmw_camera/sensors/cmw_imx335.c ****    * By default, on the MB1939 STM32N6-DK board, OVDD (1.8V) and AVDD (2.8V) are
 292:../Drivers/cmw_camera/sensors/cmw_imx335.c ****    * always on when PWR_ON is high (VDD3V3 and VCORE ON). Power-on order cannot
 293:../Drivers/cmw_camera/sensors/cmw_imx335.c ****    * be followed.
 294:../Drivers/cmw_camera/sensors/cmw_imx335.c ****    *
 295:../Drivers/cmw_camera/sensors/cmw_imx335.c ****    * MB1938 N6-DK and MB1854 IMX335 board IO mapping:
 296:../Drivers/cmw_camera/sensors/cmw_imx335.c ****    *  ShutdownPin PC8 (CN14-17) -- (CN1-17) NRST_CAM  -- 1V8 (CN2-10) RESET (XCLR?)
 297:../Drivers/cmw_camera/sensors/cmw_imx335.c ****    *  EnablePin   PD2 (CN14-18) -- (CN1-18) EN_MODULE -- 1V2 enable (CN2-6) DVDD
